		<text id="swap_text01" x="336" y="138" width="408" height="" autosize="H" style="SWAP" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Offering Choices&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;LI&gt;When parents set limits by offering choices, it can empower their child and teach consequences. &lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Some children come up with their own choice. As long as the choice moves toward the goal, accept the choice.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;The challenge with this method is that parents need to honor the child's choices, so any choice offered must be a true choice and one that the child has time to think through.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="16"&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Example:&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="16"&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;A parent could say, "You cannot wear your pajamas to school. Would you like to put on your shirt or your pants first today?" Typically, children like feeling in charge and will make &lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="16"&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;a selection.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
		</text>
		<text id="swap_text02" x="335" y="138" width="399" height="" autosize="H" style="SWAP" visible="false" fx="TEXT_SHOW" hidefx="TEXT_HIDE">
			<content translate="true">&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Using Distraction&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;As a rule of thumb, parents should follow a child's lead and be sensitive to their cues. However, in cases where a child is initiating some form of behavior that is unsafe or undesirable, it is appropriate for a parent to distract and redirect the child.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Distraction is typically an effective discipline method because toddlers and many preshoolers have short attention spans so they can be moved onto a new activity fairly easily.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="16"&gt;&lt;P ALIGN="LEFT"&gt;&lt;B&gt;Example:&lt;/B&gt;&lt;/P&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;TEXTFORMAT BLOCKINDENT="16"&gt;&lt;LI&gt;Distraction can be effective for moving a child away from electrical outlets, a hot grill, fragile items at a grandparent's house, or the toy in the store that must be left behind.&lt;/LI&gt;&lt;/TEXTFORMAT&gt;&lt;LI&gt;&lt;/LI&gt;</content>
		</text>
